<TITLE> Mexico bus crash kills 22 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MEXICO CITY, Sept 16 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A passenger bus ran off a road and fell down a ravine in the western Mexican state of Nayarit, killing 22 people and injuring 15, a Red Cross official said on Saturday. The bus tumbled down a 400-feet (120-metre) ravine after the driver fell asleep, Red Cross emergency operator Carolina Martinez said.
